headline: Davos CEO Brief for Monday, January 19, 2026
summary: WSJ Leadership Institute President Alan Murray speaks with powerful CEOs and highlights some of the top issues being discussed at the World Economic Forum in Davos this week—from geopolitical challenges to the opportunities ahead in 2026.

headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock with Exciting Potential and 2 That Underwhelm
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
